content.problemStatement:
- So far, we have learned about single-dimensional (1D) arrays (`data_type array_name[] = {value1, value2, ..., valueN};`) now, we move on to explore two-dimensional (2D) arrays.

- A 2D array in C is a collection of elements arranged in rows and columns, useful for representing tabular data such as matrices or grids. It is essentially an array of arrays where each row is a separate array.

---

**Syntax:**
```c
// Declaration and Initialization together (Static Initialization)
// Here we declare a 2D array of dataType with given rows and columns and initialize it at the same time
dataType arrayName[rows][columns] = {
    {value1, value2},
    {value3, value4}
};

// Declaration first, then Initialization (Dynamic Initialization)
// Here we declare a 2D array first without initializing it
dataType arrayName[rows][columns];
// Later, values can be assigned or accessed individually using indices, for example:
// arrayName[0][0] = accesses first row, first column → value1
// arrayName[0][1] = accesses first row, second column → value2
// arrayName[1][0] = accesses second row, first column → value3
// arrayName[1][1] = accesses second row, first column → value3
````
---

**Example:**

```c
#include

int main() {
    // Static Initialization: Predefined values
    int staticArray[2][2] = {
        {10, 20},
        {30, 40}
    };

    // Print static array as a matrix
    printf("Static Initialization:\n");
    printf("%d %d\n", staticArray[0][0], staticArray[0][1]);
    printf("%d %d\n", staticArray[1][0], staticArray[1][1]);

    // Dynamic Initialization: Declare first, then assign values
    int dynamicArray[2][2];

    // Assign values manually
    dynamicArray[0][0] = 50;
    dynamicArray[0][1] = 60;
    dynamicArray[1][0] = 70;
    dynamicArray[1][1] = 80;

    // Print dynamic array as a matrix
    printf("Dynamic Initialization:\n");
    printf("%d %d\n", dynamicArray[0][0], dynamicArray[0][1]);
    printf("%d %d\n", dynamicArray[1][0], dynamicArray[1][1]);

    return 0;
}
```
**Expected Output:**
```default
Static Initialization:
10 20
30 40
Dynamic Initialization:
50 60
70 80
````

